Cosumnes River Flow to Floodplain Habitat Area Relationship

A dataset containing the floodplain habitat area in acres as a function of flow in cubic feet per second

cosumnes_river_floodplain

Format

dataframe with 36 rows and 3 variables:

flow_cfs

integer flow value in cubic feet per second

FR_floodplain_acres

fall run floodplain acreage (use for Steelhead when needed)

watershed

name of watershed

Source

NA

Details

NA

Examples

cosumnes_river_floodplain
#> # A tibble: 35 x 3
#>    flow_cfs FR_floodplain_acres      watershed

#> 10     1610                  NA Cosumnes River
#> # ... with 25 more rows
